description:
Who among our friends and enemies will sacrifice themselves—or others—to save the world from annihilation? What will be the ultimate fate of the child Chushinmaru, a “spirit reservoir” trapped alone for 400 years in the mystical site of Karasumori?

And what is the final destiny of Karasumori’s faithful guardians, Yoshimori and Tokine...?!
name: Vol. 35

description:
Fourteen-year-old Maximum Ride, better known as Max, knows what it's like to soar above the world. She and all the members of the 'Flock' - Fang, Iggy, Nudge, Gasman and Angel - are just like ordinary kids - only they have wings and can fly. It may seem like a dream come true to some, but their lives can morph into a living nightmare at any time! Whether in the treetops of Central Park or in the bowels of the Manhattan subway system, Max and her adopted family take the ride of their lives.

Chapter 35 - 39.
name: Vol. 6

description:
Kinjiro Sakamachi is a "normal" seventeen-year-old boy who happens to suffer from an abnormal fear of women, otherwise known as gynophobia. A fateful visit to the school bathroom turns Kinjiro’s world upside down, as he discovers the dashing and popular Konoe Subaru is actually a girl!

The basis for the popular TV anime series to be released on DVD in North America by Sentai Filmworks at the end of 2012.

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 1: The Butler's Secret
  • Chapter 2: The Stray Butler and the Chicken (Me)
  • Chapter 3: Love Strikes Suddenly
  • Chapter 4: Paradise Summer
  • Chapter 5: The Wolf & the Lamb
name: Vol. 1

description: Guided only by a series of notes that direct him to do the most inexplicable things - "Buy a small turtle and throw it into the lake" - Kyon and the Mikuru from eight days in the future complete the assigned tasks, hoping that things will become clear as the SOS Brigade's adventures for that week continue. But Kyon and Mikuru's scavenger hunt soon turns to a manhunt when Mikuru is kidnapped by a group of rogue espers, time travelers, and aliens!
name: Vol. 14

description: The air of celebration surrounding 15-year-old Oz Vessalius' coming-of-age ceremony quickly turns to horror when he is condemned for a sin about which he knows nothing. He is thrown into an eternal, inescapable prison known as the Abyss from which there is no escape. There, he meets a young girl named Alice, who is not what she seems. Now that the relentless cogs of fate have begun to turn, do they lead only to crushing despair for Oz, or is there a slim sliver of hope for him to grasp?
name: Vol. 13

description:
When a new girl joins her class, Madoka Kaname feels she recognizes the mysterious, dark-haired transfer student from one of her dreams...a dream where she is approached by a cat-like creature who offers Madoka an opportunity to change destiny. Madoka had always thought magic was the stuff of fantasy...until she sees the transfer student fighting with the very cat-being from her dream! And just like in Madoka's dream, the cat gives her a choice: Will Madoka become a Puella Magi in exchange for her dearest desire? What will be the cost of having her wish come true?

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 9: They're the Ones I Just Can't Accept
  • Chapter 10: I Refuse To Rely On Anyone Anymore
  • Chapter 11: The Final Remaining Guidepost
  • Chapter 12: My Very Best Friend
name: Vol. 3

description: The forces rising to stand against Crosline are organizing as Detective Chris leads a mission to cripple their stronghold at Area 51. But in so doing, will he succeed in unleashing a terror upon humanity even sooner than was planned? Meanwhile, Irel and Lamia have reunited, but Irel finds the cursed immortal greatly changed. Is it possible that Lamia has discovered the secret to her destiny in the revelations about her past?
name: Vol. 9

description: The Uglies series goes visual in graphic novel form. This book is set in our own dystopian future and stars the 'frenemies' Shay and Tally, as well as all the major characters from the novels. Our graphic novels turn the original series on its head by revealing never-before-told details and retelling events from the point of view of Shay, the major character who truly led the revolution against the Specials.
name: Vol. 1

description: Thirteen-year-old Vladimir Tod really hates junior high. Bullies harass him, the principal is dogging him, and the girl he likes prefers his best friend. Oh, and Vlad has a secret: His mother was human, but his father was a vampire. With no idea of the extent of his powers, Vlad struggles daily with his blood cravings and his enlarged fangs. When a substitue teacher begins to question him a little too closely, Vlad worries that his cover is about to be blown. But then he faces a much bigger problem: He's being hunted by a vampire killer.
name: Vol. 1

description: Four fabulous guys must completely transform a high school into a real lady if they want to go on living rent-free in her aunt's luxurious mansion. But the girl turns out to be Sunako, the most fashion-hopeless girl in Japan, who'd rather live like a hermit and watch her favorite horror movies than undergo a makeover!
name: Vol. 29

description:
The untold tales of Atomic Robo are, uh, told! At last! Featuring Dr. Dinosaur, Sparrow, Nikola Tesla, Bruce Lee, monsters, commie bots, comic shop owners, and more!

Story Titles

  • Bloop - Art by Paul Maybury
  • City of Skulls - Art by Chris Houghton
  • Daedalus Project - Art by Zack Finfrock
  • Leaping Metal Dragon - Art by John Broglia
  • Monster Hunters - Art by Rob Reilly
  • Most Perfect Science Division - Art by Xevi Benitez
  • Once Upon A Time In China - Art by Xevi Benitez
  • Philadelphia Experiment - Art by Erica Henderson
  • Tesla's Electric Sky Schooner - Art by Gurihiru
  • The Dark Age - Art by Zack Finfrock
  • Revenger of Dr. Dinosaur - Art by Yuko Ota
  • To Kill A Sparrow - Art by Ryan Cody
  • Atomic Robo's Free Comic Book Day 2012 - Art by Scott Wegener, Colors by Matt Speroni & Zack Frinfrock
name: TPB

volume.name: Atomic Robo Presents Real Science Adventures

description: While a sinister crime organization known as FINIS plots against Bandette, the plucky young prowler receives a cryptic invitation to a midnight meeting with her greatest rival, the master thief Monsieur! Will Monsieur prove to be Bandette’s invaluable ally, or her backstabbing foe? And what will happen when a mysterious figure makes a surprise appearance at their rendezvous? Adventure! Machination! Presto!
name: Meeting At Midnight!

description: At a remote university, an angry young student faces the harsh realization that he has nothing to show for years of study. When he threatens his professor to teach him something real, he is drawn into a horrifying game of life and death. Soon, he will learn that the only rule is pain, and that true knowledge only comes when everything you believe has burned away.
name: TPB

description: From the producers of Napoleon Dynamite and The Daily Show with Jon Stewart! A group of high school outcasts, each alienated for a different reason, are thrown together as the staff of the school paper. But these kids just happen to live in Creepsville: a small retro-American town where monsters, humans, aliens, superheroes, robots, and mad scientists all live and work together.
name: GN

description: Set in the years leading up to World War II, Dreamless is a paranormal romance about an American girl and a Japanese boy who have seen each other's lives in their sleep since birth. Written by Bobby Crosby (Last Blood, Marry Me) and beautifully painted by Sarah Ellerton (The Phoenix Requiem, Th3rd World Studio's Finding Gossamyr).
name: GN

description: Make way for Claudette the giant slayer in this delightful, fantastical adventure! Claudette's fondest wish is to slay a giant. But her village is so safe and quiet! What's a future giant slayer to do? With her best friend Marie (an aspiring princess), and her brother Gaston (a pastry-chef-to-be), Claudette embarks on a super-secret quest to find a giant-without parental permission. Can they find and defeat the giant before their parents find them and drag them back home?
name: GN

description: From his earliest work written while still a teen in Northern Ireland to his American work on Preacher for DC Comics/Vertigo and The Punisher for Marvel, Garth Ennis has always had the ability to shock, titilate, and, most importantly, entertain his legion of international fans. Here is a selection of his best Judge Dredd work, including his brilliantly funny take on the Irish justice system, "The Emerald Isle," co-created with Preacher artist Steve Dillon.
name: TPB

volume.name: Judge Dredd: The Garth Ennis Collection

description: This multiple award-winning comic magazine features the hilarious misadventures of a group of gamers (the Knights) and their friends, plus useful HackMaster Basic, D&D-compatible, and other articles for games of all kinds, from tabletop to video screen. It's a slice of gamer life in strips, features and reviews, and a wonderful celebration of the gaming culture!

Now in available in Hardcover! In the early Christmas traditions of Europe, the 'Krampus' was St. Nicholas' dark servant - a hairy, horned, supernatural beast whose pointed ears and long slithering tongue gave misbehavers the creeps! This new and improved edition includes an introduction, a historical survey of the character, and over 180 lavish pre-World War 1 Krampus postcard images.
name: GN

description: Lenore discovers a new-born fruit fly, the kind that only live for one day. Reflecting on all she's seen due to her own immortality, Lenore decides to spend her life savings showing the fly one amazing day. Amusement parks, fine dining, Barcelona, and a race against time are on the menu. Will Lenore get the fly to see the world in time? Tune in or buzz out.
name: King for a Day!

description: Megaskull is part of Nobrow's Serial Box series encouraging new talent to explore narratives, worlds, and characters across bi-annually published comic books. Joining titles such as Jack Teagle's Fight! and Louis Roskosch's Leeroy and Popo, Megaskull is an invitation to witness the talents of the next wave of comics creators first.
name: GN

description: It's Phazer/Captain Action month! Two special Phazer team-ups in one titanic issue! In a unique sequel to the 1960's Captain Action toy comic, Phazer meets Captain action and together with tons of guest stars battle a new alien invasion! The flipside story features the first appearance of a new superstar as Phazer time travels, meets the World War II Captain Action, and together they take on Nazis, Imperius, and Hitler!

In an alternate reality, the dysfunctional Taylor family struggles to keep their small farm afloat after a devastating world war when a mysterious boy with a jet pack, Jet Jones, crashes into their barn, setting off a chain of events that forces them to re-evaluate what's important to them. But Jet's odd behavior causes youngest brother Oswald to suspect there is more to him than meets the eye!
name: Secrets of the Cell

has_staff_review.name: Rust Vol 2: Secrets of the Cell

description: The classic 1970s sci-fi TV series returns with all-new material! September 13, 1999. An atomic accident causes the moon to be blown out of orbit and hurled into the unknown, the survivors of the lunar base stationed there launched toward their destiny across the stars. In the wake of this disaster, Earth itself is ravaged by the scientific, environmental, and social repercussions of a world robbed of its moon. Presenting remastered classic material from the 70s with all-new material created to update the tale for a modern audience.
name: HC

description: Scott is a washed-up football player who never made it, and whose girlfriend abandoned him along with his dreams of playing pro football. But things have a way of working out, in this sweet, poetic tale - and a new chapter in Scott's life begins as the old one ends. Offered a position in a Japanese sumo training "stable," Scott abandons his old life, his old name, and even his old hair color, and becomes an aspiring sumo wrestler. And in so doing, he begins to find some kind of center in himself, a center that had seemed lost for good.
name: GN

description: Our saucy steampunk sweethearts are all "geared up" for the season in a captivating cavalcade of costumes. Their outfits may be a little brief, but they still leave plenty to the imagination. What lurks behind their masks? Dare to find out!
name: Viva La Venice

volume.name: Victorian Secret: Girls of Steampunk - Masquerade

description:
Join your GD cast favorites as they celebrate the spirit of giving (or receiving, in Peebri's case) and the spirit of adventure at the same time. May your holidays be filled with silver and Gold Digger!

Story Titles

  • Watcha Get Me?
  • A Peebo X-Mas
  • Christmas is Krampus Night
  • Twas the Night Raid Before Christmas
  • The Xmas Box

One of the longest-running and best-selling indie comic series on shelves today hits 80 issues!

Sela gets closer to unveiling the identity of the highborn within the prison walls. But not everything is as it seems and as things continue to escalate, Sela must make a choice that will affect the safety of everyone in the prison.

"The Lockdown" story-arc continues in this thrilling, action-packed issue of Grimm!
name: The Lockdown, Part 5

description: Wake the F#ck Up is the first comic from 1ok, a new imprint founded by former Marvel Publisher Bill Jemas, co-author of Ultimate Spider-Man and Origin of Wolverine, two of the bestselling graphic novels in history. This story is beautifully-illustrated by JJ Dzialowski and Cyril Saint-blancat, a talented team of up-and-coming French artists handpicked by Mr. Jemas. Printed with high-gloss covers on high quality stock, this prestige comic collectible is a great gift for parents of teens, for teens of parents, and for every comic fan.
Contains : X-Men: Schism (2011) #03-05
Batman, desperate for a lead in the Bookbinder case, turns to a very unlikely ally. Enter Catwoman!
name: Welcome to the Slough of Despond, Part 12

Contains : Ultimate Comics Spider-Man (2011) #03 , Ultimate Comics X-Men (2011) #03 , Ultimate Comics Ultimates (2011) #03
Contains : Avengers Vs. X-Men #0: Prologue

Contains : Uncanny X-Force (2010) #23 , Wolverine and the X-Men (2011) #07-08 , X-Men Legacy (2008) #264

Contains : AVX: VS (2012) #01-02

description: Volume 1 of The Complete L'il Abner contains Al Capp's comedy masterpiece from 1934-1936, including full-color Sunday pages never before collected in book form. Li'l Abner moves to New York to live with his rich aunt and has to dodge both kidnappers and grasping socialites! Then it's a classic case of mistaken identity when Li'l Abner's evil twin, the ruthless criminal Gat Garson, comes to town.
name: Volume One: 1934-1936

volume.name: Al Capp's Li'l Abner Complete Daily & Color Sunday Comics

description:
The Interceptor crew is attacked!

Hal and Razer get sucked into Myrwhydden's pocket dimension!

How will Kilowog and Aya fare against the Red Lanterns?

The Free Comic Book Day story is completed in this issue!
name: Myrwhydden

Saturday Mourning: Fly In My Eye

  • F+X=0
  • Escape from the Dead City
  • Hi-Adventure With The Contraband Commandos

name: De Kraai werpt de lont in het kruit
A Tale of Midways and Molemen

description:
Bugs Bunny makes a wrong turn at Albuquerque and winds up in the middle of a baseball game instead of Palm Springs.

Can he reach home base in time to enjoy his vacation?
name: Base On Bugs; Field of Screams; Medal Madness

description:
Bugs Bunny is running wild in a museum-and Elmer has to catch him!

What kind of impression(ism) will they make?

Has Bugs been framed?
name: Renaissance Rabbit; Snore Loser; A Hare of the Tail That Bit You;

description: The doors to the Invisible Towers are open…but who will come back out alive? To be activated, each of the towers requires the living body of a member of the quest. Their true, hidden enemies have moved the players into position and if they succeed, the world will be plunged into darkness.Will Asta and his loyal servant Badd have the power to stop this terrible plot?

When an experimental nuclear submarine is marooned deep in the Mariana Trench atop a deposit of methane ice - the most combustible substance known to man - an elite salvage team mounts a ticking-clock rescue to prevent an explosive chain reaction that could eradicate all life on Earth! From the creator of the hit Sci-Fi Channel series Eureka!
name: TPB

character_credits.name: Grand Duke Nicholas Nikolaevich of Russia

first_appearance_characters.name: Grand Duke Nicholas Nikolaevich of Russia

description: In search of another target on his list, The Arrow goes toe-to-toe with some of the most ruthless combatants the underworld has to offer.
name: Caged

description: Special sneak previews of BATMAN #15, GREEN LANTERN CORPS #15, BATGIRL #15, BEFORE WATCHMEN: RORSCHACH #3 and TEAM 7 #3! Plus, previews of all the DC comics in stores this week!

AVX tie-in! The New Avengers have received the call from Captain America to go to war against the X-Men — and Wolverine will be forced to choose a side! Then, Danny Rand discovers the shocking secret history of the Phoenix in K’un Lun’s book of the dead.
name: Volume 4

volume.name: New Avengers by Brian Michael Bendis

description: Peter Parker continues his quest to be the Ultimate Spider-Man from the Disney XD screen into your comic book pages! FIRST - No One can stop the ancient monster GARDOOM THE GARGANTUAN terrorizes New York - no one but your friendly neighborhood Spider-Man! THEN - a culinary caper as Simple Simon the Pie Man must be brought to justice by Spider-Man and the White Tiger!
name: Simon Says, Pie!; I Battled Gardoom--A Really Big Monster!

description: IDW continues their re-presentation of the entire GrimJack saga, in order. This second volume contains the first seven classic issues of First Comics's GrimJack. And as with every volume, this one features additional material in the form of character sketches, unreleased artwork, and more.
name: Volume Two

description: Where else can you study at the inter-dimensional University of Cynosure, take a bunch of Uzis to the wild, wild West and get it on with Major Lash and his Lawkillers? Timothy Truman and John Ostrander proudly represent issues eight through 14 of GrimJack, the original series, all under a brand-new hot cover painting from ol' Timbo!
name: Volume Three

description: The re-presentation of the entire First Comics GrimJack saga, in order, continues. This fourth volume delves deeper into what it means to be GrimJack and survive-hell, profit-in the insane city of Cynosure.
name: Volume Four

description: Written and drawn by creators John Ostrander and Timothy Truman, Volume 5 collects issues #22 - #30, including the special anniversary story which reunited Ostrander and Truman.
name: Volume Five

description: IDW's re-presentation of the entire classic run of First Comics GrimJack saga continues here in this sixth volume. This latest trade paperback reproduces issues 31-37 written by creator John Ostrander and illustrated by Tom Mandrake. Featuring an all-new cover by GrimJack co-creator Timothy Truman.
name: Volume Six

description: IDW continues their re-presentation of the entire First Comics GrimJack saga, in order. This seventh volume covers issues #38-46, plus "Rough Trade," a Munden's Bar story from issues #44-46. Written by co-creator John Ostrander and featuring art by Tom Mandrake. Co-creator Timothy Truman provides another all-new cover, too!
name: Volume Seven

description: At last, the entire ground-breaking GRIMJACK saga in order, beginning with the very first stories as originally published in 1983 and 1984. Come with us to Munden's Bar and meet some of the most astonishing characters in comics history.IDW continues their re-presentation of the entire First Comics GrimJack saga in this eighth volume, including issues #47-54. Written by creator John Ostrander and drawn by Tom Mandrake. Featuring an all-new cover by series co-creator Timothy Truman!
name: Volume Eight
